git clone => is a command to clone the remote repository into local machine
cd => to change the directory
ll => to see the list files and directorys
ls => is a command to view files and directorys in short list {only names}
ll -a => to see the long list of files and directorys including hidden files
git status => to see the status of the file
git add/stage => to add files to stag/index
git commit -m "message" filename
git add */stage * => used to add all the files in staging/index
git add filename filename => to add two files
git reset filename => to reset the file from staging to working directory
git => global information trackers
git is made for scm(source code manager)
git branch => to to check whether it is in main or not



